trans-unit.source: Represents a first-in, first-out collection of objects.
trans-unit.target: 表示对象的先进先出集合。

trans-unit.source: This class implements a queue as a circular array.
trans-unit.target: 此类实现队列为一个循环的数组。

trans-unit.source: Objects stored in a <xref:System.Collections.Queue> are inserted at one end and removed from the other.
trans-unit.target: 对象存储在<xref:System.Collections.Queue>某一端插入和删除来自其他。

trans-unit.source: Queues and stacks are useful when you need temporary storage for information; that is, when you might want to discard an element after retrieving its value.
trans-unit.target: 当你需要为信息; 临时存储时，队列和堆栈非常有用也就是说，当你可能想要检索其值后放弃元素。

trans-unit.source: Use <xref:System.Collections.Queue> if you need to access the information in the same order that it is stored in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 使用<xref:System.Collections.Queue>如果你需要访问集合中存储的相同顺序的信息。

trans-unit.source: Use <xref:System.Collections.Stack> if you need to access the information in reverse order.
trans-unit.target: 使用<xref:System.Collections.Stack>如果你需要按相反的顺序访问的信息。

trans-unit.source: Use <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601> or <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentStack%601> if you need to access the collection from multiple threads concurrently.
trans-unit.target: 使用<xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentQueue%601>或<xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentStack%601>如果你需要同时从多个线程访问集合。

trans-unit.source: Three main operations can be performed on a <xref:System.Collections.Queue> and its elements:
trans-unit.target: 可以对执行三个主要操作<xref:System.Collections.Queue>及其元素：

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Enqueue%2A> adds an element to the end of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Enqueue%2A> 将元素添加到的末尾<xref:System.Collections.Queue>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Dequeue%2A> removes the oldest element from the start of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Dequeue%2A> 从开始处移除最旧的元素<xref:System.Collections.Queue>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Peek%2A> returns the oldest element that is at the start of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> but does not remove it from the <xref:System.Collections.Queue>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Peek%2A> 返回在开始时的最旧元素<xref:System.Collections.Queue>但不会删除从<xref:System.Collections.Queue>。

trans-unit.source: The capacity of a <xref:System.Collections.Queue> is the number of elements the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> can hold.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue>是元素的数目<xref:System.Collections.Queue>可以保存。

trans-unit.source: As elements are added to a <xref:System.Collections.Queue>, the capacity is automatically increased as required through reallocation.
trans-unit.target: 如元素添加到<xref:System.Collections.Queue>，自动增加容量通过重新分配所需的方式。

trans-unit.source: The capacity can be decreased by calling <xref:System.Collections.Queue.TrimToSize%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 可以通过调用减少容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue.TrimToSize%2A>。

trans-unit.source: The growth factor is the number by which the current capacity is multiplied when a greater capacity is required.
trans-unit.target: 增长因子是的数是当前容量的乘数需要更大的容量时。

trans-unit.source: The growth factor is determined when the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> is constructed.
trans-unit.target: 确定增长因子时<xref:System.Collections.Queue>构造。

trans-unit.source: The default growth factor is 2.0.
trans-unit.target: 默认增长因子为 2.0。

trans-unit.source: The capacity of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> will always increase by at least a minimum of four, regardless of the growth factor.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue>将始终按 4 的倍数，而不考虑增长因子至少达到了最小值增加。

trans-unit.source: For example, a <xref:System.Collections.Queue> with a growth factor of 1.0 will always increase in capacity by four when a greater capacity is required.
trans-unit.target: 例如，<xref:System.Collections.Queue>增长因子为 1.0 会始终增加容量由 4 个需要更大的容量时。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Queue> accepts `null` as a valid value and allows duplicate elements.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Queue> 接受`null`作为有效的值，并允许重复的元素。

trans-unit.source: For the generic version of this collection, see <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601?displayProperty=nameWithType>
trans-unit.target: 此集合的泛型版本，请参阅 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601?displayProperty=nameWithType>

trans-unit.target: 下面的示例演示如何创建并将值添加到<xref:System.Collections.Queue>以及如何打印出其值。

trans-unit.source: Public static (<see langword="Shared" /> in Visual Basic) members of this type are thread safe.
trans-unit.target: 公共静态 (<see langword="Shared" />在 Visual Basic 中) 的此类型的成员都是线程安全。

trans-unit.source: Any instance members are not guaranteed to be thread safe.
trans-unit.target: 但不保证所有实例成员都是线程安全的。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee the thread safety of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" />, all operations must be done through the wrapper returned by the <see cref="M:System.Collections.Queue.Synchronized(System.Collections.Queue)" /> method.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保的线程安全性<see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" />，所有操作必须通过返回的包装器来都完成<see cref="M:System.Collections.Queue.Synchronized(System.Collections.Queue)" />方法。

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举整个集合本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 即使某个集合已同步，其他线程仍可以修改该集合，这会导致枚举数引发异常。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举期间锁定集合，或者捕获由其他线程进行的更改所导致的异常。

trans-unit.source: Creates a shallow copy of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" />.
trans-unit.target: 创建 <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" /> 的浅表副本。

trans-unit.source: A shallow copy of the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" />.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" /> 的浅表副本。

trans-unit.source: A shallow copy of a collection copies only the elements of the collection, whether they are reference types or value types, but it does not copy the objects that the references refer to.
trans-unit.target: 集合的浅表副本复制仅的元素集合，不论它们是引用类型还是值类型，但它不会复制引用所引用的对象。

trans-unit.source: The references in the new collection point to the same objects that the references in the original collection point to.
trans-unit.target: 新集合中的引用都指向原始集合中的引用指向同一对象。

trans-unit.source: In contrast, a deep copy of a collection copies the elements and everything directly or indirectly referenced by the elements.
trans-unit.target: 与此相反，集合的深层副本复制这些元素，以及由这些元素直接或间接引用的所有内容。

trans-unit.target: 此方法通过调用可确定相等性<xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>。

trans-unit.source: This method performs a linear search; therefore, this method is an O(`n`) operation, where `n` is <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 此方法执行的线性搜索;因此，此方法为 O (`n`) 操作，其中`n`是<xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Starting with the .NET Framework 2.0, this method uses the collection’s objects’ <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A> and <xref:System.IComparable.CompareTo%2A> methods on `obj` to determine whether `item` exists.
trans-unit.target: 从.NET Framework 2.0 开始，此方法使用集合的对象<xref:System.Object.Equals%2A>和<xref:System.IComparable.CompareTo%2A>方法`obj`以确定是否`item`存在。

trans-unit.source: In the earlier versions of the .NET Framework, this determination was made by using the <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A> and <xref:System.IComparable.CompareTo%2A> methods of the `obj` parameter on the objects in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 在.NET Framework 的早期版本，通过进行此决定<xref:System.Object.Equals%2A>和<xref:System.IComparable.CompareTo%2A>方法`obj`参数的集合中的对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A> is the number of elements that are actually in the <xref:System.Collections.Queue>.

trans-unit.source: The capacity of a <xref:System.Collections.Queue> is always greater than or equal to <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue>始终是大于或等于<xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A> exceeds the capacity while adding elements, the capacity is automatically increased by reallocating the internal array before copying the old elements and adding the new elements.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>添加元素时超过容量，通过在复制旧元素和添加新的元素之前重新分配在内部数组自动增加容量。

trans-unit.source: The new capacity is determined by multiplying the current capacity by the growth factor, which is determined when the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> is constructed.
trans-unit.target: 新的容量取决于当前容量乘以增长因子，这是确定何时<xref:System.Collections.Queue>构造。

trans-unit.source: The capacity of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> will always increase by a minimum value, regardless of the growth factor; a growth factor of 1.0 will not prevent the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> from increasing in size.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue>始终将增加最小值，而不考虑增长因子; 将不会阻止 1.0 增长因子<xref:System.Collections.Queue>从大小在增加。

trans-unit.source: As elements are added to a <xref:System.Collections.Queue>, the capacity is automatically increased as required through reallocation.

trans-unit.source: The growth factor is the number by which the current capacity is multiplied when a greater capacity is required.
trans-unit.target: 增长因子是的数是当前容量的乘数需要更大的容量时。

trans-unit.source: The growth factor is determined when the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> is constructed.

trans-unit.source: The capacity of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> will always increase by a minimum value, regardless of the growth factor; a growth factor of 1.0 will not prevent the <xref:System.Collections.Queue> from increasing in size.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Queue>始终将增加最小值，而不考虑增长因子; 将不会阻止 1.0 增长因子<xref:System.Collections.Queue>从大小在增加。

trans-unit.target: 如果在内部数组需要可重新分配以容纳新元素，此方法会成为 O (`n`) 操作，其中`n`是<xref:System.Collections.Queue.Count%2A>。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: C# 语言的 `foreach` 语句（在 Visual Basic 中为 `for each`）隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 也会将枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，未定义 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.target: 获取一个值，该值指示是否同步对 <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" /> 的访问（线程安全）。

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if access to the <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" /> is synchronized (thread safe); otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: 如果对 <see langword="true" /> 的访问是同步的（线程安全），则为 <see cref="T:System.Collections.Queue" />；否则为 <see langword="false" />。

trans-unit.source: The default is <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: 默认值为 <see langword="false" />。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee the thread safety of the <xref:System.Collections.Queue>, all operations must be done through the wrapper returned by the <xref:System.Collections.Queue.Synchronized%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保的线程安全性<xref:System.Collections.Queue>，所有操作必须通过返回的包装器来都完成<xref:System.Collections.Queue.Synchronized%2A>方法。

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举整个集合本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 即使某个集合已同步，其他线程仍可以修改该集合，这会导致枚举数引发异常。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举期间锁定集合，或者捕获由其他线程进行的更改所导致的异常。
